# TypeScript and TSX files

- Use `for...of` syntax over `.forEach`
- Always follow best practices for DRY and typesafe code
- Prevent repeating code, search for existing functionality first
- Separate logical components, do not put styles in with display code, or lookup code
- Always run typechecking using `pnpm run check <filename>` after saving a file
- DO NOT override types
- DO NOT use `as any` conversions to avoid type warnings
- DO use `zod` when creating data types, and `z.infer` to create Typescript interfaces
- DO prefer proper typing when possible
